Nice! Want to do something similar or try something a bit different? Here are quick options. Tell me which one you’d like (or give your own parameters), and I’ll run it.

- Generate another random number in the same range (1–100)
- Random integer in a custom range [a, b] (tell me a and b)
- Random float between 0 and 1
- Generate N random integers in a range (e.g., N=5, range 1–100)
- Pick a random item from a list you provide
- Generate a random password (length and character set you choose)
- Seeded run for reproducibility (pass a seed like 42)
- Save the result to a file (e.g., results.txt)
